1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,000
Have you seen Darryl?

2
00:00:01,000 --> 00:00:03,000
He's around here somewhere.

3
00:00:03,000 --> 00:00:05,000
Hmm.

4
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:07,000
Yeah, Darryl's here.

5
00:00:07,000 --> 00:00:08,000
So is Santa Claus.

6
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:11,000
It's just a regular Thursday.

7
00:00:11,000 --> 00:00:14,000
Neither guy is here, and it's Friday.

8
00:00:14,000 --> 00:00:18,000
Welcome to me and Darryl's world of lies.

9
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:22,000
Nobody knows it yet, but Darryl already started working in Philly.

10
00:00:22,000 --> 00:00:24,000
So now he has to sneak out of here

11
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:28,000
like the sneakiest little sneaky sneak you ever saw.

12
00:00:29,000 --> 00:00:33,000
And I'm his helper. It's so fun.

13
00:00:33,000 --> 00:00:34,000
Hi, Darryl.

14
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:39,000
Here are your full-color printouts for this business.

15
00:00:41,000 --> 00:00:44,000
Hey, Erin, I'm going to the bathroom.

16
00:00:44,000 --> 00:00:45,000
Take your time.

17
00:00:45,000 --> 00:00:47,000
Normally I don't do shady stuff,

18
00:00:47,000 --> 00:00:50,000
but seeing as Andy's been gone three months

19
00:00:50,000 --> 00:00:53,000
and Clark took some sort of sexification,

20
00:00:53,000 --> 00:00:55,000
I figure I can cut loose a little.

21
00:00:55,000 --> 00:00:57,000
I'm good at it, too.

22
00:00:58,000 --> 00:01:02,000
Darryl, meet Bear-l.

23
00:01:02,000 --> 00:01:04,000
How much did you pay for that?

24
00:01:04,000 --> 00:01:06,000
Nothing. Won him at the carnival.

25
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:08,000
Spent a ton on tickets, though.

26
00:01:08,000 --> 00:01:09,000
Drive safe.

27
00:01:09,000 --> 00:01:11,000
Everybody knows I go to Philly.

28
00:01:11,000 --> 00:01:13,000
I've just been using sick days I saved up,

29
00:01:13,000 --> 00:01:16,000
but Erin was so excited about being sneaky sneaks,

30
00:01:16,000 --> 00:01:18,000
I went along with it.

31
00:01:18,000 --> 00:01:21,000
Ha ha ha! Darryl, you are too much!

32
00:01:21,000 --> 00:01:24,000
That guy's hilarious. He's here today.

33
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:41,000
You're kidding. You have to work Saturday and Sunday?

34
00:01:41,000 --> 00:01:43,000
Yeah, maybe you could come up here.

35
00:01:43,000 --> 00:01:45,000
I could get us into the Sixers practice facility.

36
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:47,000
You could see Cece working on her dunks.

37
00:01:47,000 --> 00:01:48,000
Maybe see you guys for dinner.

38
00:01:48,000 --> 00:01:50,000
Yeah, well, I was kind of hoping to work on my mural this weekend.

39
00:01:50,000 --> 00:01:53,000
I mean, I want to get it finished so I can start working on the other one.

40
00:01:53,000 --> 00:01:55,000
Blow it off. I haven't seen you guys in days.

41
00:01:55,000 --> 00:01:56,000
You blow it off.

42
00:01:56,000 --> 00:01:58,000
Ma'am, I'm not saying murals aren't important.

43
00:01:58,000 --> 00:01:59,000
But?

44
00:01:59,000 --> 00:02:02,000
Nothing. I'm just not saying they're not important.

45
00:02:02,000 --> 00:02:04,000
Okay, good, because it kind of sounded like you were going to say

46
00:02:04,000 --> 00:02:07,000
that murals are important but not as important as something else.

47
00:02:07,000 --> 00:02:10,000
Well, I certainly did not say that. Only a fool would say that.

48
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:13,000
Yes, only a fool would. Good save, helper.

49
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:16,000
I've really been putting in the hours on this mural.

50
00:02:16,000 --> 00:02:19,000
And my boss is totally okay with it because he's in the Bahamas

51
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:22,000
and has no clue what anybody's doing.

52
00:02:22,000 --> 00:02:25,000
I'm usually very self-critical. I hate what I paint,

53
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:29,000
but I don't know. This time I feel like it's really coming together.

54
00:02:29,000 --> 00:02:31,000
Oh, my God!

55
00:02:31,000 --> 00:02:34,000
Well, you've got to be kidding me.

56
00:02:34,000 --> 00:02:37,000
What? Are those butts?

57
00:02:37,000 --> 00:02:39,000
Huh?

58
00:02:39,000 --> 00:02:41,000
No way.

59
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:43,000
No way!

60
00:02:43,000 --> 00:02:45,000
Excuse me, everyone.

61
00:02:45,000 --> 00:02:48,000
Is it okay if I leave early from work today?

62
00:02:48,000 --> 00:02:52,000
It's Philip's first birthday, and the senator and I are hosting a party at our house.

63
00:02:52,000 --> 00:02:54,000
Oh, cute.
